]], {{Esccnty|Georgia|y=2018}}'s representatives in the Eurovision Song Contest 2018, did a rendition of the song.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2KUjxQfmOEY|title=\u201e\u10d8\u10e0\u10d8\u10d0\u10dd\u10e1\u201c \u10e1\u10d0\u10e9\u10e3\u10e5\u10d0\u10e0\u10d8 \u10d4\u10d5\u10e0\u10dd\u10de\u10d4\u10da \u10db\u10d0\u10e7\u10e3\u10e0\u10d4\u10d1\u10d4\u10da\u10e1! IRIAO - Amar Pelos Dois (Salvador Sobral)|website=[[YouTube]]|date=April 30, 2018}}</ref>\n* In a tribute at the Eurovision Song Contest 2018, several 2017 contestants sang the song: [[Svala]] ({{Esccnty|Iceland|y=2017}}), [[Manel Navarro]] ({{Esccnty|Spain|y=2017}}), [[Norma John]] ({{Esccnty|Finland|y=2017}}), [[Alma (French singer)|Alma]] ({{Esccnty|France|y=2017}}), [[Kristian Kostov]] ({{Esccnty|Bulgaria|y=2017}}), [[Martina B\u00e1rta]] ({{Esccnty|Czech Republic|y=2017}}), and [[Blanche (singer)|Blanche]] ({{Esccnty|Belgium|y=2017}}).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Kzwz36iITqw|title=Throwback to Salvador Sobral's Amar Pelos Dois in Kyiv|website=[[YouTube]]|date=May 8, 2018}}</ref>\n* [[Michael Schulte (singer)|Michael Schulte]], {{Esccnty|Germany|y=2018}}'s representative in the Eurovision Song Contest 2018, covered the song in a reception held by the German embassy in [[Lisbon]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=meRiqW4uZlY|title=Michael Schulte singt \"Amar Pelos Dois\" von Salvador Sobral / Eurovision Song Contest / NDR|website=[[YouTube]]|date=May 10, 2018}}</ref>\n* Brazilian singer [[:pt:Lilian Rodrigues|Lilian Rodrigues]] recorded a cover of the song.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=CdYTqWmt3LQ|title=Amar Pelos Dois|website=[[YouTube]]|date=August 10, 2018}}</ref>\n* [[Tiziana Tosca Donati]], winner of the [[Sanremo Music Festival 1996]], recorded an Italian-language version for her album ''Morabeza''.<ref>{{Facebook|TizianaToscaDonatiOfficial/videos/10156716253803896/|name=Tiziana Tosca Donati}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|